CHARLES B. MOLING CO. et al. v. KNIGHT et al. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. December 18, 1916.) No. 2885. In Error to the District Court of the United States for the Southern District of Texas; Waller T. Burns, Judge. Presley K. Ewing, of. Houston, Tex., for plaintiffs in error. Sam Streetman, of Houston, Tex., for defendants in error.

Before PARDEE and WALKER, Circuit Judges, and FOSTER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

We find no reversible error in the proceedings in this case, and none of the assignments of error are well taken. Judgment affirmed.
